	<Title>
		Recipe: Asian vegetable salad
	</Title>
	<Abstract>
		Bok choy, red cabbage, cashews and snow peas combine to make a visually stunning salad.
	</Abstract>
	<ServingInfo Label="Serves">
		4
	</ServingInfo>
	<DietitianTip Label="Dietitian&apos;s tip">
		&lt;strong&gt;Dietitian&apos;s tip:&lt;/strong&gt; This recipe uses several knife techniques &amp;mdash; julienne, chiffonade, mince and chop &amp;mdash; to bring together a lovely and tasty salad.
	</DietitianTip>
	<Directions Label="Directions">
		&lt;p&gt;
Rinse all vegetables under cold running water. Let drain. 
&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;
Julienne (cut into very thin strips like match sticks) carrot, bell pepper, bok choy and yellow onion. 
&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;
Chiffonade (cut across grain into very narrow thin strips) cabbage and spinach. 
&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;
Mince (cut into tiny pieces) garlic. Then chop (cut into slightly larger pieces) cilantro and cashews. 
&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;
Place vegetables, cilantro, cashews and snow peas in a large bowl. Drizzle with sesame oil and soy sauce. Toss well to combine. Serve. 
&lt;/p&gt;
	</Directions>
	<Ingredients Label="Ingredients">
		&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;1 1/2 cup carrot&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;1/2 cup red bell pepper&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;1 1/2 cup bok choy&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;1/2 cup yellow onion&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;1 cup red cabbage&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;1 1/2 cup spinach&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;1 tablespoon garlic&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;1 tablespoon cilantro&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;1 1/2 tablespoons cashews&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;1 1/2 cups snow peas&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;2 teaspoons toasted sesame oil&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;2 teaspoons low-sodium soy sauce&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
	</Ingredients>
